        JavaScript Document Object Model (DOM)
          - allows programs and scripts to dynamically access and update the content, structure and style of a document.

        Finding HTML elements
          - document.getElementById ("id"); -> would only return one element since IDs should be unique.
          - document.getElementsByClassName ("class"); -> would need to use loop since it might return more than one element; all elements with that classname
          - document.getElementsByTagName ("tag"); -> would need to use loop since it might return more than one element; all elements with that tag

        Changing Attributes
          - you can change attributes of tags by directly accessing that attribute
          - e.g. document.getElementById ("icon").src = "new.jpg";

        Changing Styles
          - you can change the style by accessing the style attribute
          - e.g. document.getElementById ("icon").style.color = red;
